We reiterated our last and prior years’ recommendations that the Local Chief Executive require:

The Inventory Committee to conduct physical count of properties and equipment for each Office/Department; 

The Property/Supply Officer-Designee to reconcile the listed properties and equipment/RPCPPE to the Property Cards pertaining thereto and finalize the List of Properties and Equipment for each Office/Department;

The Municipal Accountant to reconcile the Inventory Report for PPE with the Property Ledger Cards, and make a summary of unserviceable property and equipment with the corresponding cost/values;

The Municipal Engineer together with the Inventory Committee to conduct inventory of Buildings and other physical structures of the Municipality and submit the inventory to the Municipal Accountant who shall reconcile the report with the Properly Ledger Cards; 

The Municipal Accountant to prepare a summary of all noted property and equipment, including buildings and other physical structures, not found during the physical count and coordinate with the Property/Supply Officer-Designee and the Municipal Engineer for the status of the same, including buildings and other physical structures; and

 The Inventory Committee to submit to the Auditor together with the physical inventory report, a report for unserviceable property and equipment and non-existing buildings and other physical structure with their corresponding cost/values.

We recommended that the Municipal Treasurer:

Require all COs to turn over all collections intact at the close of business each day with the corresponding RCD together with the duplicate copies of the ORs;

Verify the cash collections turned over to her by the COs against the duplicate ORs and the RCD;

Require the COs to strictly issue ORs according to their numerical sequence;

Monitor the movement of the AFs in the custody of the AOs by requiring them to prepare the Monthly Report of Accountability for Accountable Forms (MRAAFs); and,

In addition to recording her transactions in the computer, shall still maintain the prescribed Cashbook to facilitate verification thereof by the Audit Team and to have a permanent record of her transactions, pursuant to Section 63 of the LTOM.

We recommended that Management require the Accountant:

To prepare and submit the Monthly Trial Balance and Quarterly FS, together with Schedules and Annexes, on or before the prescribed timelines in accordance with the abovementioned rules and regulations;

To recommend for hiring additional qualified personnel to the Accounting Office and to allow the personnel of the Accounting Office to attend trainings or Seminars relative to their works, in order to equip them with the required knowledge and skills and to continue improving their performance.

